cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a protocol for interactive topic modeling using anchor words, which is a popular technique in machine learning. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as topic modeling is often used in information retrieval tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and text analysis. It may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as topic modeling is a common technique in AI research. Finally, it could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as topic modeling is often used in analyzing social networks and online communities.
